namespace kindergarten_garden {

std::vector<std::string> plants(const std::string& diagram, const std::string& student) {
    // List of children in order
    const std::vector<std::string> children = {
        "Alice", "Bob", "Charlie", "David",
        "Eve", "Fred", "Ginny", "Harriet",
        "Ileana", "Joseph", "Kincaid", "Larry"
    };
    
    // Find the index of the student
    std::int32_t index = 0;
    for (std::int32_t i = 0; i < static_cast<std::int32_t>(children.size()); i++) {
        if (children[i] == student) {
            index = i;
            break;
        }
    }
    
    // Split the diagram into lines
    std::vector<std::string> rows;
    std::istringstream iss(diagram);
    std::string line;
    while (std::getline(iss, line)) {
        rows.push_back(line);
    }
    
    // We should have exactly two rows
    if (rows.size() < 2) {
        // Handle error case, but according to the problem, there should be two rows
        return {};
    }
    
    const std::string& row1 = rows[0];
    const std::string& row2 = rows[1];
    
    // Get the plants for the child
    std::vector<std::string> result;
    
    // For each plant code, map to full name
    std::map<char, std::string> plant_map = {
        {'G', "grass"},
        {'C', "clover"},
        {'R', "radishes"},
        {'V', "violets"}
    };
    
    // Calculate positions
    std::int32_t pos = 2 * index;
    
    // First row plants
    result.push_back(plant_map[row1[pos]]);
    result.push_back(plant_map[row1[pos + 1]]);
    
    // Second row plants
    result.push_back(plant_map[row2[pos]]);
    result.push_back(plant_map[row2[pos + 1]]);
    
    return result;
}

}  // namespace kindergarten_garden

    // List of children in order

        "Eve", "Fred", "Ginny", "Harriet",

        }

    // Split the diagram into lines
    std::vector<std::string> rows;
    std::istringstream iss(diagram);
    std::string line;

    // We should have exactly two rows

        return {};

    const std::string& row1 = rows[0];
    const std::string& row2 = rows[1];
    
    // Get the plants for the child

    // Second row plants

    result.push_back(plant_map[row2[pos + 1]]);
    
    return result;
}
